\f0\b\fs54 \cf2 Meat Loaf
\fs48 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs28 \cf2 Yield: 
\b0 6 servings\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs48 \cf2 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl420\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs38 \cf2 {\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon good olive oil\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 cups chopped yellow onions (3 onions)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon chopped fresh thyme leaves\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons kosher salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/3 cup canned chicken stock or broth\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon tomato paste\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 1/2 pounds ground chuck (81 percent lean)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup plain dry bread crumbs (recommended: Progresso)\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 extra-large eggs, beaten\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup ketchup (recommended: Heinz)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs48 \cf2 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa180\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs38 \cf2 Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F.\
Heat the olive oil in a medium saute pan. Add the onions, thyme, salt, and pepper and cook over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, for 8 to 10 minutes, until the onions are translucent but not brown. Off the heat, add the Worcestershire sauce, chicken stock, and tomato paste. Allow to cool slightly.\
In a large bowl, combine the ground chuck, onion mixture, bread crumbs, and eggs, and mix lightly with a fork. Don't mash or the meat loaf will be dense. Shape the mixture into a rectangular loaf on a sheet pan covered with parchment paper. Spread the ketchup evenly on top. Bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, until the internal temperature is 160 degrees F and the meat loaf is cooked through. (A pan of hot water in the oven, under the meat loaf, will keep the top from cracking.) Serve hot.\
